RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 1 1M Dirt CR: 74. Starter Allowance Purse 20000. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since June 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since May 5 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $5,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CUENCA set a pressured pace on the inside, drew clear leaving the three eighths while still in hand, then was given three pops right handed with the crop leaving the furlong marker and drew off to prove much the best. BLIND SIGHT tracked the pace from the inside, shifted off the rail and tried to go with the winner on the turn, but could not keep pace and proved to be no match for that rivals, second best. TERPEYE was settled early and two wide on the backstretch, shifted out and made a four wide run on the turn, but had no late rally, bested rest. PSYCHE pressed the pace three to two wide and tired.

ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked pace inside, bid 2 wide 1/4, no match, 2nd best

ENTRY.COMMENT: allowed to settle, 2 wide 1/2, 4 wide 1/4 pole, bested rest

ACT OF VALOR was settled early, four wide on the turn and had no rally. INDEFATIGABLE was reserved early andf failed to menace. NAUTICAL NATURE was not a threat on the inside. CALL WIL chased the pace three wide and weakened.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 3 1 1/16M Turf CR: 76. Allowance Purse 28000. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR PENNSYLVANIA BRED. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since June 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since May 5 Allowed 4 lbs. (Races Where Entered For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances) Preference to horses with the most starts at Penn National since May 31st 2022. (If deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile and One Sixteenth.).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: ON THE SHORTLIST was away alertly to set the pace towards the inside, was well handled and in the two path on the turn and drew off when sent down leaving the turn, then was kept to a mild drive to prove much the best. STRONG GEM was rated along two wide early, then dropped to the inside on the backstretch, saved ground on the turn and was put down leaving the turn but proved to be no match for the winner, second best. SIDESWIPED stalked the winner four wide, faded in the drive while staying on for the show award. SURPRISINGLY SWEET was well placed early, then went up to stalk the pace three wide and weakened in the drive. CALL ON CLARA was forced out four wide into the first turn, then settled into stride, advanced on the turn and eased out and came six wide into the lane and had no rally. SASSY MARTINI chased the pace three wide and then was two wide on the turn and weakened. A CASE OF YOU chased the early pace and then checked and got out into the first turn, dropped back and was not a threat. MELODIA was reserved on the inside and tired. HEYBACKATCHA was settled early and then tired. There was a STEWARDS INQUIRY into the running into the first turn, after reviewing the replays the race was left as is.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: PENN NATIONAL RACE 4 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 88. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 22000. (PLUS UP TO 40% PABF) FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $25,000 OR LESS AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $25,000 AND WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 122 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mile Or Over Since June 5 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since May 5 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000 (Races Where Entered For $16,000 Or Less Not Considered In Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: KAZ PALACE broke outwardly at the start, then recovered and was sent to the front to set a fast pace while clear, got to the inside and remained clear while getting into a good rhythm on the backstretch, then was still clear off the turn, was given a pop left handed but drifted out from that, then was corrected with a pop right handed and then moved back in, then widened the margin late despite being erratic in the lane to prove best. CRITICAL THINKING chased the pace from between rivals on the fist turn, three wide on the turn and came four wide into tbe drive and was up for the place award. JUMP FOR THE WIN chased the pace on the inside of a trio, then was two wide on the backstretch and advanced on the turn and came three wide into then drive but faded the final furlong. TUSKEGEE CAT chased the pace on the outside and was four to five wide on the turn and tired.

ENTRY.COMMENT: chased pace inside, 2 wide turn, lacked late response,

RACE.FOOTNOTES: HASHTAG WINNING was settled back early, three to four wide on the backstretch, dropped to the inside and saved ground entering the far turn by the three eighths, then shifted out and made a four wide run on the turn, shifted out when straighten to close well on the outside and get up late to prove best, driving. SHANGHAI CANDY was reserved early, then moved up outside and five wide on the backstretch, four wide on the turn and made a bid off the turn and led in the furlong grounds but was caught late, good effort. WAHOOWA WAHOOWA set the early pace while two wide, then was rated entering the backstretch, dueled for the lead by the half mile marker, continued to duel on the turn and then was between rivals by the furlong marker and fought on gamely to the wire to stay for the show award. LAKE NAKURU was settled early, made a middle move on the inside and dueled for command on the inside on the turn, then gained a short lead by the furlong marker but faded late. A T M AWESOME stalked the early pace and then went up to press the pace three wide, faded in the drive. SUPER DUDE was settled early, then chased the pace between rivals and two wide and then weakened. FLAT OUT FLASHY chased the early pace, then had a four wide pursuit on the backstretch and tired.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: KAREN'S WAY dueled for the lead on the inside, then rated off the duel on the turn, bumped leaving the turn while making a bid, gained a short lead by the furlong marker and shook clear, then held on late to prove best, driving. FIELD LETTERS was settled early, two wide on the turn, eased out and came five wide into the lane, closed well on the outside but could not get to the winner late, second best. HALLIGIRL chased the pace from the inside, came three wide into the lane, then was between rivals and bumped a rival by the sixteenth marker and got the show award late. HIT A HOMER HONEY chased the pace three wide, advanced and came four wide into the lane, was between foes by the furlong marker, then was bumped by the sixteenth marker and missed the show award. ONE TOUGH ROSE dueled for the lead with the winner and made a two wide bid to gain a short lead by the five sixteenths marker, then exchanged bumps with that rival leaving the quarter pole, then faded the final furlong. SMOKE AND MIRRORS was settled on the inside, swung out wide leaving the turn and stopped.
